<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-27T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-27T06:44:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.00/832: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hall</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-27T11:00:00-00:44">June 27, 1930—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>89. My 88, June 25, 4 p.m. Barclay sent the documents to the Legation
                            this morning and inquired as to their authenticity. I replied that they
                            were forgeries and asked what steps the Liberian Government was taking
                            to ascertain their source.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hall</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>